In Underscore 1.5, [_.after](https://github.com/jashkenas/underscore/issues/364) changed from

``` js
_.after = function(times, func) {
  if (times <= 0) return func();
  return function() {
    if (--times < 1) {
      return func.apply(this, arguments);
    }
  };
};
```

to

``` js
_.after = function(times, func) {
  return function() {
    if (--times < 1) {
      return func.apply(this, arguments);
    }
  };
};
```

This means if `times` is less than `1` it will no longer execute immediately.
See https://github.com/jashkenas/underscore/issues/982.

